HEADWORD: Diaheliotropism
<hw>Di`a*he`li*ot"ro*pism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A tendency of leaves or other organs of plants to
have their dorsal surface faced towards the rays of light.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

